text: Group I of the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification tournament was one of the 12 groups to decide the teams which qualify for the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations finals tournament. The group consisted of four teams: Burkina Faso, Angola, Botswana, and Mauritania. The teams played against each other in home- and-away round-robin format between June 2017 and March 2019. Angola and Mauritania, the group winner and runner-up, qualified for the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations. ==Standings== ==Matches== \---- \---- \---- \---- \---- ==Goalscorers== ==Notes== ==References== ==External links== *32nd Edition Of Total Africa Cup Of Nations, CAFonline.com Group I
